# platform_adaptation.me
# Purpose: iOS vs Android differences and required functional equivalents. Defines
#          where platform-native implementations are acceptable and where exact
#          parity is required. This file does NOT redefine product behaviour —
#          see system_contracts.me and ux_parity.me for that.
# Scope: iOS (SwiftUI/UIKit), Android (Jetpack Compose / native Android APIs)

---

## 1. PRINCIPLE

Platform-native implementation is expected and encouraged where it produces a better
user experience. What must not vary is the product outcome: same data, same business
logic trigger points, same user-facing messaging.

---

## 2. PAYMENTS — STRIPE

### iOS
- `StripePaymentSheet` (native iOS Stripe SDK)
- Apple Pay configured with `merchantId: "merchant.com.bookadink"`, `merchantCountryCode: "AU"`
- `StripeAPI.defaultPublishableKey` set at app init from `SupabaseConfig.stripePublishableKey`
- PaymentSheet result: `.completed`, `.canceled`, `.failed`

### Android Equivalent Required
- `PaymentSheet` from Stripe Android SDK (`com.stripe:stripe-android`)
- Google Pay configured as a payment method (equivalent to Apple Pay)
- Same merchant country: `AU`
- Same publishable key (from `SupabaseConfig`)
- PaymentSheet result must map to: completed, canceled, failed — with identical downstream logic

### Non-negotiable for both platforms
- PaymentIntent is created by `create-payment-intent` Edge Function — not locally
- `application_fee_amount` is computed by the Edge Function — not by the client
- Booking row is inserted ONLY on `.completed` result — never on `.canceled` or `.failed`
- Both platforms pass `{ gameID, userID, creditsToApply, currency }` to the Edge Function

---

## 3. PUSH NOTIFICATIONS — APNs vs FCM

### iOS
- APNs (Apple Push Notification service)
- Token registered at app launch, stored server-side per user
- Notification tap routing handled in `NotificationsView` via `navigationDestination`

### Android Equivalent Required
- FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging)
- Token registered at app launch, stored server-side per user
- Supabase Edge Functions must be updated to send to both APNs and FCM tokens
- `club-chat-push`, `booking-confirmed`, `game-cancelled-notify`, `waitlist-promoted`, `send-review-prompts` Edge Functions all need Android FCM support
- Notification tap routing must match iOS: clubs navigate inline, games open as modal

### Payload structure (same on both platforms)
```json
{
  "title": "...",
  "body": "...",
  "data": {
    "type": "booking_confirmed | game_cancelled | waitlist_promoted | club_announcement | club_chat_mention | club_chat_reply | game_review_request",
    "gameID": "uuid | null",
    "clubID": "uuid | null"
  }
}
```

### UUID normalisation in Edge Functions
- All UUIDs in notification payloads sent from Edge Functions must be lowercased
- iOS bug fix (April 2026): notification delivery was broken because UUID case mismatch prevented routing — apply same lowercasing on Android targets

