## 4. DEEP LINKING

### iOS
- Custom URL scheme: `bookadink://`
- Registered in `Info.plist` and handled in `BookADinkApp`
- Handled cases: `club/{id}`, `game/{id}`, `booking/{id}`, `review/{gameID}`
- `DeepLink.review(gameID:)` — handled as no-op (review prompts come via notifications only)

### Android Equivalent Required
- Intent filter for `bookadink://` scheme in `AndroidManifest.xml`
- Same path patterns: `club/{id}`, `game/{id}`, `booking/{id}`, `review/{gameID}`
- App Links (HTTPS deep links) for share URLs — same host/path as iOS
- `review/{gameID}` — no-op on Android as well (notification-only flow)

---

## 5. LOCATION SERVICES

### iOS
- `LocationService.swift` / `CLLocationManager`
- Used for: NearbyGamesView, NearbyDiscoveryView
- Permission: "when in use" only

### Android Equivalent Required
- `FusedLocationProviderClient` (Google Play Services)
- Same permission level: `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` with runtime request
- Same use cases: nearby games, nearby clubs
- Location not sent to server — used client-side for sorting/filtering only

---

## 6. IN-APP BROWSER

### iOS
- `SafariView` (wraps `SFSafariViewController`)
- Used for: Stripe Connect onboarding, pickleball news articles

### Android Equivalent Required
- Chrome Custom Tabs (`androidx.browser:browser`)
- Same use cases: Stripe Connect onboarding URL, news article URLs
- Do NOT open in system browser (no back navigation) — use in-app browser only

---

## 7. LOCAL NOTIFICATIONS

### iOS
- `LocalNotificationManager.swift` using `UNUserNotificationCenter`
- Used for: waitlist hold countdown reminder ("30 minutes to complete your booking")

### Android Equivalent Required
- `NotificationManager` + `AlarmManager` or `WorkManager` for scheduled local notifications
- Same trigger: when player is promoted to `pending_payment`, schedule a reminder at `holdExpiresAt - 5 minutes`
- Cancel scheduled local notification when hold is confirmed or expires

---

## 8. STORAGE — USERDEFAULTS vs SharedPreferences

### iOS
- `UserDefaults` keyed by `StorageKeys.*`
- `StorageKeys.duprRatingsByUserID` → `[userIDString: {d: Double, s: Double}]` (JSON)

### Android Equivalent Required
- `SharedPreferences` or `DataStore<Preferences>` (prefer DataStore for new Android code)
- Same key namespace: `duprRatingsByUserID`
- Same structure: map of userID (lowercased string) to `{doubles: Double, singles: Double}`
- Sync from Supabase `profiles.dupr_rating` after every profile fetch (same as iOS)

---

## 9. IMAGE LOADING AND UPLOAD

### iOS
- `AsyncImage` for remote URLs
- Upload via Supabase Storage SDK to `club-images` bucket
- Paths: `club-avatars/{clubID}/{uuid}.jpg`, `club-banners/{clubID}/{uuid}.jpg`

### Android Equivalent Required
- Coil or Glide for remote image loading
- Upload via Supabase Storage REST API (multipart/form-data POST)
- Same bucket name: `club-images`
- Same path structure: `club-avatars/{clubID}/{uuid}.jpg`, `club-banners/{clubID}/{uuid}.jpg`
- Same dimension hints: avatar 400×400 px, banner 1500×500 px (3:1 ratio)
- Validate upload URL against allowed Supabase host before rendering

---

## 10. SUBSCRIPTION MANAGEMENT (Club Owner)

### iOS
- Stripe PaymentSheet for subscription activation
- `create-club-subscription` Edge Function → returns `client_secret`
- Status displayed in Club Settings sheet

### Android Equivalent Required
- Same Stripe PaymentSheet flow (Stripe Android SDK)
- Same Edge Function (`create-club-subscription`) — no Android-specific backend changes
- Same status states: `incomplete`, `active`, `past_due`, `canceled`
- Google Play Billing is NOT used — Stripe handles all subscription billing on both platforms

---

## 11. FONT AND ICON SYSTEMS

### iOS
- SF Symbols for icons
- System font (San Francisco)

### Android Equivalent
- Material Symbols or Material Icons for Android-equivalent icons
- Roboto or system font
- Icon semantic meaning must match: same icon for same action across platforms
- Named mappings (iOS SF Symbol → Android Material equivalent):
  - `person.fill` → `account_circle`
  - `calendar` → `calendar_today`
  - `mappin` → `location_on`
  - `bell.fill` → `notifications`
  - `creditcard` → `credit_card`
  - `star.fill` → `star`

---

## 12. FEATURES NOT YET ON ANDROID (DO NOT IMPLEMENT IN V1)

These features exist on iOS but are not in scope for Android v1:
- DUPR rating history chart (`DUPRHistoryCard`)
- Apple Pay (Android has Google Pay — implement via Stripe Android SDK)
- Splash screen video (`splash.mp4`) — use static splash on Android
- "Win Rate" stat in profile — no data backing; blocked on both platforms

---

## VIOLATION IMPACT
- Booking row inserted before PaymentSheet `.completed` on Android → same production issue as iOS.
- Using global credit balance instead of club-scoped → cross-club credit spending.
- Sending Android push via APNs (wrong service) → 100% delivery failure on Android.
- Opening Stripe Connect URL in system browser → no back navigation; user abandons onboarding.
- Not lowercasing UUIDs in notification payloads → notification tap routing fails silently.
